Police say that the two persons might have died of Covid-19 complications.A post-mortem report from the government pathologist differs. In a twist of fate, two men who were arrested for flouting the 10pm curfew died after spending a night in police cells in Kirinyaga County.
But while police say that the two, Martin Musyoka, 58, and John Njeru, 28, might have died of Covid-19 complications, a post-mortem report from the government pathologist differs, saying the pair died of either internal injuries or lack of oxygen.



