It all started on November 20 this year when the two villagers were detained during a crackdown on people who were flouting curfew rules imposed by the government to prevent the spread of Covid-19 in Kirinyaga County.
The villagers were seized in Mikimaini and Thiba villages in Mwea East Sub-County and locked up at Wang'uru police station.
However, the following day they collapsed in the cells as they waited to be arraigned in court and were rushed to Kimbimbi Sub-County Hospital where they died during treatment.



