Moments later, police said that the two might have succumbed to the Covid-19 disease.
The county police commander Leah Kithei told the media that the remand prisoners fell sick when they were at the station and were taken to hospital.
She dismissed claims by relatives that they had been assaulted while in the cells.
She also denied claims that the duo was in crowded cells and might, therefore, have suffocated to death.
Mwea East Sub-County police head Daniel Kitavi also denied that the two villagers had been attacked at the station.
He said the villagers were among five remand prisoners who were found ailing in the cells.
"The two remand prisoners succumbed while being treated and we suspected they died of Covid-19 because they complained of difficulty in breathing," said Mr Kitavi.



